1
00:01:35,990 --> 00:01:38,289
[Too Young To Love]

2
00:01:38,440 --> 00:01:41,220
[Episode 12]

3
00:01:45,289 --> 00:01:46,620
Why did you call me here?

4
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:50,560
Do you think...

5
00:01:51,130 --> 00:01:52,660
Shan likes you?

6
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,880
Do I think Shan likes me?

7
00:01:57,259 --> 00:01:58,039
Or rather,

8
00:01:59,259 --> 00:02:01,280
has Shan ever told you he likes you?

9
00:02:01,900 --> 00:02:02,670
No.

10
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:05,970
Has he ever contacted you first?

11
00:02:10,870 --> 00:02:12,250
Ever given you a gift?

12
00:02:13,470 --> 00:02:14,910
Do the drinks and cake

13
00:02:14,940 --> 00:02:16,000
he bought me count?

14
00:02:18,180 --> 00:02:19,740
Do you think they count?

15
00:02:21,030 --> 00:02:21,680
No.

16
00:02:22,310 --> 00:02:23,030
Then

17
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,200
has he ever...

18
00:02:25,870 --> 00:02:27,079
tried to

19
00:02:27,079 --> 00:02:29,170
find chances to be alone with you?

20
00:02:29,470 --> 00:02:30,240
No.

21
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:33,740
Why are you suddenly asking all this?

22
00:02:34,310 --> 00:02:37,470
He never said he liked you,

23
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:39,920
never reached out to you first,

24
00:02:39,920 --> 00:02:41,200
never gave you a gift,

25
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:44,310
and didn't even want to be alone with you.

26
00:02:45,470 --> 00:02:46,710
So, is it possible

27
00:02:47,150 --> 00:02:48,150
that Shan

28
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:51,980
just sees you as

29
00:02:52,750 --> 00:02:53,920
a friend?

30
00:02:56,920 --> 00:02:58,030
Just a friend?

31
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:06,660
I looked it up online this afternoon too.

32
00:03:07,030 --> 00:03:09,030
They say that when a guy likes a girl,

33
00:03:09,710 --> 00:03:11,370
it mainly shows in these ways:

34
00:03:12,030 --> 00:03:13,430
He gets jealous over her,

35
00:03:15,690 --> 00:03:17,760
shares his life with her,

36
00:03:18,590 --> 00:03:20,710
and gets possessive of her.

37
00:03:21,310 --> 00:03:21,920
And...

38
00:03:22,710 --> 00:03:24,970
the guy actively apologizes to the girl.

39
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:27,440
He doesn't seem to do any of that.

40
00:03:33,150 --> 00:03:35,079
I have a basketball game
in a couple of days.

41
00:03:35,079 --> 00:03:36,880
Remember to come and cheer me on.

42
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:38,079
Of course.

43
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:41,560
If there's nothing else, I'll head out.

44
00:03:50,870 --> 00:03:51,829
I've already

45
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:53,710
adjusted the exposure on all these photos.

46
00:03:53,710 --> 00:03:55,150
Want to get them developed together?

47
00:03:55,150 --> 00:03:56,610
They're all photos of you.

48
00:03:57,590 --> 00:03:58,520
So will these...

49
00:03:58,990 --> 00:04:01,200
appear immediately after developing?

50
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:03,110
Mm.

51
00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:04,590
That magical?

52
00:04:05,590 --> 00:04:06,640
I want to try.

53
00:04:11,150 --> 00:04:12,150
Teach me.

54
00:04:13,030 --> 00:04:13,710
So...

55
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:15,200
do I...

56
00:04:16,519 --> 00:04:18,250
put the whole picture in first?

57
00:04:18,519 --> 00:04:18,880
Yes.

58
00:04:19,029 --> 00:04:20,360
Just put it in this tray.

59
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:24,160
♪ I watch the rain drift softly
over the city ♪

60
00:04:23,320 --> 00:04:24,450
-And then?
-Then...

61
00:04:24,450 --> 00:04:28,570
♪ As if you took all the sunshine with you
when you left ♪

62
00:04:26,350 --> 00:04:28,610
hold the tray steady and shake it gently.

63
00:04:28,740 --> 00:04:32,560
♪ The old lanes we walked
are flooded with memories of us ♪

64
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:30,840
Slower.

65
00:04:32,760 --> 00:04:33,270
Like this.

66
00:04:32,810 --> 00:04:36,430
♪ Now, I just stand here
as lovers brush past me ♪

67
00:04:34,710 --> 00:04:36,150
Shake it gently

68
00:04:36,710 --> 00:04:39,080
so the developer flows evenly.

69
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:40,900
♪ Some remain forever young and free ♪

70
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:45,040
♪ In their eyes, I see you and me ♪

71
00:04:45,190 --> 00:04:49,210
♪ The lonely air surrounds me ♪

72
00:04:49,670 --> 00:04:52,000
♪ Shutting out the noise
and all the warmth ♪

73
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:53,270
Amazing.

74
00:04:52,490 --> 00:04:55,659
♪ Leaving only silence ♪

75
00:04:53,590 --> 00:04:55,520
The image appeared instantly.

76
00:04:56,950 --> 00:05:00,530
♪ I wish I could be a goldfish ♪

77
00:05:01,020 --> 00:05:04,840
♪ With its so-called seven-second memory ♪

78
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:06,920
♪ Seven was the moment we first met ♪

79
00:05:06,030 --> 00:05:07,270
You made me look so good.

80
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:08,960
♪ Six was when we grew close ♪

81
00:05:08,710 --> 00:05:09,970
You've always been beautiful.

82
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:11,550
♪ Now, there's just an empty space
beside me ♪

83
00:05:21,580 --> 00:05:22,660
I just remembered,

84
00:05:23,030 --> 00:05:25,690
I still have homework to finish
back at the dorm.

85
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:27,700
I'll go back first.

86
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:29,640
See you at the basketball game.

87
00:05:29,640 --> 00:05:30,060
Okay.

88
00:05:33,370 --> 00:05:36,970
♪ I wish I could be a goldfish ♪

89
00:05:37,280 --> 00:05:41,120
♪ With its so-called seven-second memory ♪

90
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:43,210
♪ Seven was the moment we first met ♪

91
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:45,260
Is something wrong with my heart lately?

92
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:45,220
♪ Six was when we grew close ♪

93
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:49,690
♪ Now, there's just an empty space
beside me where you should be ♪

94
00:05:45,640 --> 00:05:48,240
Why does my heart race
every time I see someone?

95
00:05:49,590 --> 00:05:50,740
I should probably go to the hospital
and get it checked.

96
00:05:49,770 --> 00:05:53,480
♪ I wish I could be a goldfish ♪

97
00:05:54,020 --> 00:05:57,640
♪ So I wouldn't be swallowed
by memories anymore ♪

98
00:05:57,940 --> 00:05:59,710
♪ Five was all the hugs we shared ♪

99
00:06:00,070 --> 00:06:01,820
♪ Four was the moment we broke up ♪

100
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:09,330
♪ Three, two, one,
and I can finally forget you ♪

101
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:04,970
I'm back at the dorm.

102
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:06,400
Go to bed early.

103
00:06:20,470 --> 00:06:22,150
Why are you lifting such a heavy weight?

104
00:06:22,150 --> 00:06:23,480
You have to start light.

105
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:26,180
I can handle it.

106
00:06:33,909 --> 00:06:37,510
Did your girlfriend say your muscles are
too small or something?

107
00:06:51,840 --> 00:06:53,170
Come on, let me help you.

108
00:06:53,710 --> 00:06:54,310
Thanks...

109
00:06:54,470 --> 00:06:55,400
You're welcome.

110
00:06:59,590 --> 00:07:00,960
I got here first!

111
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:12,080
Xiaole.

112
00:07:12,840 --> 00:07:14,150
You saved a practice room for me?

113
00:07:14,150 --> 00:07:15,120
You're so nice!

114
00:07:15,270 --> 00:07:17,200
I know you can't get one on your own.

115
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:18,910
Go in and practice.

116
00:07:18,910 --> 00:07:19,970
I won't bother you.

117
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:26,710
Luo, give me a hand here!

118
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:28,080
Oh, coming.

119
00:07:39,270 --> 00:07:41,000
Luo, the guests here have left!

120
00:07:41,960 --> 00:07:42,520
Coming.

121
00:08:05,710 --> 00:08:07,640
Ning, you're going out?

122
00:08:08,150 --> 00:08:08,710
Where are you going?

123
00:08:08,710 --> 00:08:09,710
Let me carry those for you.

124
00:08:09,710 --> 00:08:10,270
No need.

125
00:08:10,710 --> 00:08:13,080
Why'd you come to my school
without saying anything?

126
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:14,550
I missed you.

127
00:08:14,710 --> 00:08:15,710
Let me carry those.

128
00:08:15,710 --> 00:08:16,510
Really, no...

129
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:22,630
Why...

130
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:25,060
are you carrying so many bags?

131
00:08:26,150 --> 00:08:27,840
I'm going to sell them
at the secondhand market.

132
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,030
Do you need to buy something?

133
00:08:29,030 --> 00:08:30,430
I can buy it for you first.

134
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:33,409
This is my own business.

135
00:08:35,710 --> 00:08:36,320
Then...

136
00:08:38,510 --> 00:08:40,640
I already drove here. Let me drive you.

137
00:08:42,510 --> 00:08:43,039
Let's go.

138
00:08:50,350 --> 00:08:50,990
Ning,

139
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:52,800
if you're having any difficulties,

140
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:54,040
you can just tell me.

141
00:08:54,510 --> 00:08:55,870
I really can help you.

142
00:08:59,110 --> 00:09:00,710
Sometimes I really envy you—

143
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:02,860
nothing seems to be a problem for you.

144
00:09:03,280 --> 00:09:05,140
I hope you can always be like this.

145
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:08,390
Also,

146
00:09:08,750 --> 00:09:10,990
don't drive a sports car
to my school anymore.

147
00:09:10,990 --> 00:09:12,520
You don't go to this school.

148
00:09:12,750 --> 00:09:13,680
It's too flashy.

149
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:20,800
Is it?

150
00:09:24,510 --> 00:09:25,870
I'll get going then!

151
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:29,680
I just feel like

152
00:09:30,630 --> 00:09:32,560
Ning doesn't feel anything for me.

153
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,800
If she didn't have feelings for you,

154
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:36,870
why would she date you?

155
00:09:40,920 --> 00:09:43,780
Then why is it
that every time I come looking for her,

156
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:45,470
she says she's busy?

157
00:09:46,230 --> 00:09:48,560
And she never talks to me about her life.

158
00:09:49,630 --> 00:09:52,360
Is it possible
that she just doesn't want to say it

159
00:09:52,390 --> 00:09:53,870
or can't say it?

160
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:56,440
Why do you have to know anyway?

161
00:09:58,510 --> 00:10:00,500
It's not that I have to know,

162
00:10:00,630 --> 00:10:02,920
but aren't relationships supposed to be
about supporting each other?

163
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:04,040
Just like my parents—

164
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:05,350
they talk about everything,

165
00:10:05,350 --> 00:10:08,610
and when they run into problems,
they solve them together.

166
00:10:10,560 --> 00:10:13,360
Something has happened
with her family recently.

167
00:10:13,510 --> 00:10:15,840
It's understandable that she doesn't...

168
00:10:16,230 --> 00:10:18,160
want to talk about certain things.

169
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:21,960
Then tell me,

170
00:10:22,990 --> 00:10:24,120
what should I do now?

171
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:32,160
See? You don't know either.

172
00:10:33,390 --> 00:10:35,390
But I think for things like this,

173
00:10:35,390 --> 00:10:37,450
you have to find the answer yourself.

174
00:10:37,920 --> 00:10:40,280
I just can't find it!

175
00:10:44,510 --> 00:10:45,640
You like her, right?

176
00:10:45,750 --> 00:10:46,210
Yeah.

177
00:10:46,350 --> 00:10:48,280
Then being with her must make you happy.

178
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:48,750
Yeah!

179
00:10:49,160 --> 00:10:52,510
Then just care for her
and look after her every day.

180
00:10:52,510 --> 00:10:53,640
One day,

181
00:10:54,160 --> 00:10:56,360
when she wants to talk, she'll tell you.

182
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:59,920
But I feel like
she doesn't need my concern.

183
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:02,440
She makes me feel completely useless.

184
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:03,510
Just like what my parents say—

185
00:11:03,510 --> 00:11:04,680
I can just kick back

186
00:11:04,680 --> 00:11:06,540
as a rich kid and not lift a finger.

187
00:11:09,870 --> 00:11:11,470
I really envy your life.

188
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:13,440
Ning said the same thing.

189
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:14,630
Can you help me figure out

190
00:11:14,630 --> 00:11:16,960
how to get closer to her?

191
00:11:18,750 --> 00:11:21,350
I'd like someone to help me.

192
00:11:22,990 --> 00:11:23,920
Something's up?

193
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:26,230
What could be up?

194
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:27,540
What are you two doing?

195
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:32,380
According to my analysis,

196
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:35,560
Ning is a girl with a lot of pride.

197
00:11:36,390 --> 00:11:38,440
She doesn't easily accept help
from others.

198
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:39,560
With a lot of things,

199
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:41,490
you can't be too direct with her.

200
00:11:42,750 --> 00:11:43,390
But

201
00:11:43,920 --> 00:11:46,280
when you show you care,

202
00:11:46,630 --> 00:11:48,960
you can be a little more straightforward.

203
00:11:49,630 --> 00:11:51,430
Are you writing a thesis or what?

204
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:52,510
What are you even talking about?

205
00:11:52,510 --> 00:11:55,570
What do you mean
by all this "direct or not direct" talk?

206
00:11:55,750 --> 00:11:58,160
Girls are just a bit complicated.

207
00:11:58,160 --> 00:12:00,290
How can you not understand Ning at all?

208
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:03,450
It's still because you don't
understand her.

209
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:05,710
The point is, she has never

210
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:07,950
talked to me about herself.

211
00:12:08,560 --> 00:12:10,220
Every time we go out, it's just

212
00:12:10,350 --> 00:12:11,350
eating together,

213
00:12:11,630 --> 00:12:12,630
and then I crack a few jokes

214
00:12:12,630 --> 00:12:15,040
and share a few memes to make her laugh.

215
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:18,440
Now that I think about it,

216
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:20,090
it seems like...

217
00:12:20,750 --> 00:12:22,680
we've never even had a proper date.

218
00:12:23,710 --> 00:12:25,840
They've never been on a proper date...

219
00:12:26,160 --> 00:12:27,650
So what?

220
00:12:28,390 --> 00:12:30,160
If she didn't have feelings for you,

221
00:12:30,160 --> 00:12:31,750
she wouldn't be dating you.

222
00:12:32,680 --> 00:12:33,160
Didn't I

223
00:12:33,510 --> 00:12:34,680
just say that?

224
00:12:37,370 --> 00:12:39,090
Before we started dating,

225
00:12:39,110 --> 00:12:41,630
I felt pretty relaxed around her.

226
00:12:41,630 --> 00:12:43,090
But after we got together,

227
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:43,960
I feel like...

228
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:46,230
every day I'm just

229
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:48,420
walking on eggshells,

230
00:12:48,510 --> 00:12:50,570
trying to do things to make her happy.

231
00:12:53,230 --> 00:12:54,680
This relationship of yours

232
00:12:54,680 --> 00:12:56,210
sounds really exhausting.

233
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:00,810
Don't be such a wet blanket.

234
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:06,800
Ning's been pretty busy these days.

235
00:13:06,920 --> 00:13:08,710
How about when she's free, I'll help you

236
00:13:08,710 --> 00:13:09,510
sound her out?

237
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:11,390
I guess that's the only way.

238
00:13:13,040 --> 00:13:14,040
I'm going to class.

239
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:14,770
See you guys.

240
00:13:16,990 --> 00:13:17,990
Leaving already?

241
00:13:23,990 --> 00:13:27,870
I have to say,
you're way too much of a coward.

242
00:13:27,870 --> 00:13:30,920
Still zero progress since high school?

243
00:13:31,230 --> 00:13:32,160
Who says?

244
00:13:33,230 --> 00:13:34,560
Mind your own business.

245
00:13:35,920 --> 00:13:38,720
I'm telling you, to win a girl over,
you need to act.

246
00:13:38,990 --> 00:13:41,560
Take action—action is everything!

247
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:49,640
Let me go find the one.

248
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:02,000
Your piano's broken?

249
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:04,220
They sent you to fix the piano?

250
00:14:05,110 --> 00:14:06,240
I'll take you there.

251
00:14:14,390 --> 00:14:16,390
You're really here to fix the piano?

252
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:17,510
Why else?

253
00:14:19,870 --> 00:14:21,400
I thought you came to see me.

254
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:25,000
I'm really here to fix the piano.

255
00:14:43,560 --> 00:14:44,160
I...

256
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:46,260
forgot to bring the parts.

257
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:48,280
Oh.

258
00:14:50,230 --> 00:14:51,160
I really forgot.

259
00:14:51,680 --> 00:14:52,160
Mmhmm.

260
00:14:56,390 --> 00:14:56,860
So...

261
00:14:57,350 --> 00:14:57,920
I'll

262
00:14:58,230 --> 00:14:59,560
go back and get them now.

263
00:15:01,040 --> 00:15:01,570
Go ahead.

264
00:15:17,560 --> 00:15:18,760
I'll go with you then.

265
00:15:21,780 --> 00:15:22,040
T-That's

266
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:22,630
fine.

267
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:38,040
Nice shot!

268
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:46,080
What are you looking at?

269
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:48,210
The game is over?

270
00:15:49,230 --> 00:15:49,590
Cool!

271
00:15:55,510 --> 00:15:56,840
I think I just saw Shan.

272
00:15:57,280 --> 00:15:57,920
Shan?

273
00:15:58,750 --> 00:15:59,680
I don't think so.

274
00:15:59,870 --> 00:16:01,400
Didn't I play well just now?

275
00:16:01,630 --> 00:16:02,390
You did.

276
00:16:03,040 --> 00:16:03,510
Xiaole!

277
00:16:06,680 --> 00:16:08,010
Show us what you've got.

278
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:09,770
Watch out, there's a girl here.

279
00:16:11,510 --> 00:16:12,370
That scared me.

280
00:16:12,630 --> 00:16:14,110
I definitely saw Shan.

281
00:16:15,280 --> 00:16:16,410
Why didn't I see him?

282
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:18,060
Are you seeing things?

283
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:19,280
Fine.

284
00:16:19,750 --> 00:16:21,280
I'm heading to his shop now.

285
00:16:21,280 --> 00:16:21,910
See you.

286
00:16:23,870 --> 00:16:25,390
I'm going there too.

287
00:16:25,390 --> 00:16:27,350
Why don't you wait for me to change first?

288
00:16:27,350 --> 00:16:29,010
I just got a new batch of books.

289
00:16:29,230 --> 00:16:29,850
Let's go.

290
00:16:55,110 --> 00:16:56,230
Can you find them?

291
00:16:57,630 --> 00:16:58,430
Just a moment.

292
00:17:34,150 --> 00:17:35,720
Uh, sorry.

293
00:17:36,190 --> 00:17:37,320
The parts haven't arrived yet.

294
00:17:37,320 --> 00:17:40,120
It might take a few days
before we can install them.

295
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:43,450
You still have feelings for me.

296
00:17:44,150 --> 00:17:44,590
Huh?

297
00:17:48,080 --> 00:17:49,810
You still have feelings for me.

298
00:17:51,630 --> 00:17:52,560
What do you want?

299
00:18:22,670 --> 00:18:23,480
Shh.

300
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:25,600
What's wrong?

301
00:18:26,390 --> 00:18:28,050
What's wrong? What happened?

302
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:42,130
Why did you leave without saying goodbye?

303
00:18:42,950 --> 00:18:44,410
Haven't you always known?

304
00:18:48,240 --> 00:18:49,390
So now...

305
00:18:52,630 --> 00:18:53,480
you regret it?

306
00:19:35,190 --> 00:19:37,560
What? What?

307
00:19:37,910 --> 00:19:38,630
What did you see?

308
00:19:38,630 --> 00:19:39,670
Tell me, quickly.

309
00:19:39,670 --> 00:19:40,910
Let me eat a candy to calm my nerves.

310
00:19:40,910 --> 00:19:41,630
You have one too.

311
00:19:41,630 --> 00:19:42,800
Why should I eat one?

312
00:19:42,800 --> 00:19:46,200
I'm afraid what I'm about to say
might give you a heart attack.

313
00:19:46,910 --> 00:19:47,970
Can you tell me now?

314
00:19:50,080 --> 00:19:51,150
Tell me.

315
00:19:51,150 --> 00:19:53,950
-Let me swallow first!
-Hurry up! What did you see?

316
00:20:00,390 --> 00:20:01,190
Professor Ye?

317
00:20:01,390 --> 00:20:02,390
Stay here.

318
00:20:03,150 --> 00:20:04,040
Professor Ye!

319
00:20:13,220 --> 00:20:14,330
Professor Ye Mei!

320
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:18,540
What a coincidence. Why are you here?

321
00:20:18,720 --> 00:20:20,310
I'm here to pick up parts for the piano.

322
00:20:20,310 --> 00:20:21,800
I work part-time
at this musical instrument store.

323
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:23,800
Just come to me if you need anything.

324
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:26,360
Has your boss ever mentioned me?

325
00:20:26,720 --> 00:20:28,560
No. Are you friends?

326
00:20:29,390 --> 00:20:30,050
Never mind.

327
00:20:32,390 --> 00:20:33,590
Goodbye, Professor.

328
00:20:40,560 --> 00:20:41,000
Shan,

329
00:20:41,840 --> 00:20:43,790
are you and Professor Ye dating?

330
00:20:49,630 --> 00:20:50,760
We're just friends.

331
00:20:52,390 --> 00:20:53,390
"Just friends"?

332
00:20:53,560 --> 00:20:54,000
Mm.

333
00:20:58,590 --> 00:20:59,150
Fine.

334
00:21:00,390 --> 00:21:01,190
Let me ask you,

335
00:21:01,390 --> 00:21:02,350
do you like Lan?

336
00:21:08,840 --> 00:21:10,150
Do you want me to say

337
00:21:10,350 --> 00:21:11,430
yes

338
00:21:11,840 --> 00:21:12,840
or no?

339
00:21:14,350 --> 00:21:15,880
Whether you like her or not,

340
00:21:16,320 --> 00:21:17,920
keep your distance from her.

341
00:21:20,390 --> 00:21:21,670
So, you like Lan.

342
00:21:22,870 --> 00:21:23,290
Right?

343
00:21:24,110 --> 00:21:25,590
She doesn't know yet, does she?

344
00:21:25,590 --> 00:21:27,390
Do you need me to tell her for you?

345
00:21:29,190 --> 00:21:30,320
That's my business.

346
00:21:32,190 --> 00:21:33,910
Shan Liwei, I'm warning you.

347
00:21:34,630 --> 00:21:36,110
If you dare hurt Yi Lan,

348
00:21:36,670 --> 00:21:38,400
I won't let you get away with it.

349
00:21:38,910 --> 00:21:40,710
You won't let me get away with it?

350
00:21:40,790 --> 00:21:43,630
You don't even have the courage
to confess your feelings.

351
00:21:43,630 --> 00:21:45,290
You call that liking someone?

352
00:21:51,320 --> 00:21:52,350
Shan, I'm here.

353
00:21:52,910 --> 00:21:53,640
You're here!

354
00:21:55,190 --> 00:21:55,780
Shan.

355
00:21:56,150 --> 00:21:58,350
Here, have a nougat. It'll cheer you up.

356
00:22:06,870 --> 00:22:07,240
Mm.

357
00:22:09,150 --> 00:22:10,150
So sweet.

358
00:22:12,430 --> 00:22:13,110
Lan.

359
00:22:14,560 --> 00:22:16,350
Later I'll order your favorite—

360
00:22:16,350 --> 00:22:16,910
pizza.

361
00:22:17,110 --> 00:22:17,970
How about that?

362
00:22:18,390 --> 00:22:19,800
Sure.

363
00:22:20,080 --> 00:22:21,160
Thanks, Shan.

364
00:22:21,320 --> 00:22:22,580
You're the best, Shan.

365
00:22:23,080 --> 00:22:24,010
You're welcome.

366
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:29,350
Shan,

367
00:22:29,350 --> 00:22:30,730
let's go see a movie this weekend.

368
00:22:30,730 --> 00:22:31,490
My treat.

369
00:22:31,630 --> 00:22:32,100
Sure.

370
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:33,980
Pick whatever you want. My treat.

371
00:22:34,390 --> 00:22:35,250
What do you want to watch?

372
00:22:35,250 --> 00:22:36,290
My treat.

373
00:22:39,240 --> 00:22:41,140
This is going to be a date
just for Shan and me.

374
00:22:41,140 --> 00:22:42,630
I'm warning you, stay out of it.

375
00:22:42,630 --> 00:22:43,430
Shan.

376
00:22:43,480 --> 00:22:44,080
Didn't you say

377
00:22:44,080 --> 00:22:46,080
we could all watch a movie together?

378
00:22:46,480 --> 00:22:46,950
Shan,

379
00:22:46,950 --> 00:22:48,910
didn't you say we'd watch a movie alone?

380
00:22:48,910 --> 00:22:50,390
Yeah, alone.

381
00:22:51,480 --> 00:22:52,480
I want to come too.

382
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:53,630
Tong Xiaole!

383
00:22:57,430 --> 00:22:58,150
Where are you going?

384
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:58,170
[Father and Son]

385
00:22:58,460 --> 00:23:02,290
[Father and Son]

386
00:22:58,800 --> 00:22:59,630
Heading back to school!

387
00:22:59,630 --> 00:23:00,890
Carry the cello for me!

388
00:23:02,820 --> 00:23:03,230
[Father and Son]

389
00:23:12,970 --> 00:23:15,960
[Father and Son]

390
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:23,390
Yi Lan!

391
00:23:28,560 --> 00:23:29,150
Lan!

392
00:23:32,800 --> 00:23:33,590
Yi Lan!

393
00:23:36,300 --> 00:23:38,150
Why did you have to interfere?

394
00:23:38,390 --> 00:23:40,190
Do you really not want me to date?

395
00:23:40,350 --> 00:23:40,950
I'm warning you—

396
00:23:40,950 --> 00:23:42,000
if you keep interfering,

397
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,110
you'll regret it!

398
00:23:45,150 --> 00:23:45,610
What...

399
00:23:47,080 --> 00:23:47,800
What did I do?

400
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:49,670
Can't you see I like Shan?

401
00:23:52,240 --> 00:23:53,150
I know.

402
00:23:54,950 --> 00:23:56,010
But I don't know...

403
00:23:56,390 --> 00:23:56,850
what...

404
00:23:56,910 --> 00:23:58,710
what exactly you like about him.

405
00:23:59,910 --> 00:24:02,440
What I like about him
is none of your business.

406
00:24:05,110 --> 00:24:07,070
Anyway, you're my best friend.

407
00:24:07,630 --> 00:24:10,230
At worst, I'll just bring you along
on my dates.

408
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:13,400
You'll bring me along...

409
00:24:14,430 --> 00:24:15,240
on your dates?

410
00:24:16,320 --> 00:24:18,910
Don't you have a girl you've liked
since high school?

411
00:24:18,910 --> 00:24:20,150
I'll help you chase her.

412
00:24:20,150 --> 00:24:22,590
Once you're dating,
the four of us can hang out together.

413
00:24:22,590 --> 00:24:23,150
Happy?

414
00:24:24,390 --> 00:24:24,920
Let's go.

415
00:24:39,720 --> 00:24:40,920
I bought this for you.

416
00:24:44,800 --> 00:24:45,630
What is it?

417
00:24:45,950 --> 00:24:47,240
A new card wallet.

418
00:24:47,630 --> 00:24:49,030
Yours is all worn out.

419
00:24:53,910 --> 00:24:54,430
Thanks.

420
00:24:55,390 --> 00:24:55,920
Let's go.

421
00:24:58,390 --> 00:24:59,920
Why are you walking so fast?

422
00:25:03,150 --> 00:25:06,080
Before I fell in love with you,
I'd forgotten your kiss—

423
00:25:06,080 --> 00:25:08,410
yet my heart always remembered your lips.

424
00:25:11,190 --> 00:25:12,080
Nice poem.

425
00:25:19,430 --> 00:25:20,230
What's wrong?

426
00:25:23,590 --> 00:25:24,480
Today,

427
00:25:25,190 --> 00:25:27,390
I just wanted to give you a chance
to impress her.

428
00:25:27,390 --> 00:25:28,990
I didn't expect to scare her.

429
00:25:30,080 --> 00:25:30,740
Is she okay?

430
00:25:32,080 --> 00:25:32,740
She's fine.

431
00:25:39,720 --> 00:25:41,630
Still nothing between you two?

432
00:25:43,150 --> 00:25:43,530
Look,

433
00:25:43,950 --> 00:25:46,150
as your bro, let me give you another tip.

434
00:25:46,150 --> 00:25:47,850
Find another girl

435
00:25:48,150 --> 00:25:49,390
and pretend to get close to her

436
00:25:49,390 --> 00:25:50,520
to make Lan jealous.

437
00:25:50,910 --> 00:25:52,240
I guarantee it'll work.

438
00:25:53,870 --> 00:25:55,280
Thank you.

439
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:58,560
Stop dragging your feet.

440
00:25:58,630 --> 00:26:00,780
Just be direct and confess to her.

441
00:26:01,320 --> 00:26:01,870
Remember,

442
00:26:01,870 --> 00:26:04,000
girls hate wishy-washy guys the most.

443
00:26:04,890 --> 00:26:05,490
Be a man.

444
00:26:20,180 --> 00:26:22,510
Xiaole, what are you doing here?

445
00:26:23,350 --> 00:26:24,390
I have something to tell you.

446
00:26:24,390 --> 00:26:25,240
What is it?

447
00:26:25,240 --> 00:26:27,040
I need to go grab a practice room.

448
00:26:27,480 --> 00:26:28,210
Come with me.

449
00:26:30,910 --> 00:26:31,630
What for?

450
00:26:32,190 --> 00:26:34,190
I still need to grab a practice room!

451
00:26:35,560 --> 00:26:37,080
What's so urgent?

452
00:26:43,450 --> 00:26:45,240
I need to grab a practice room!

453
00:26:45,870 --> 00:26:46,670
What's wrong?

454
00:26:54,630 --> 00:26:57,230
Isn't this a photo of the two of us
from the ball?

455
00:26:59,590 --> 00:27:00,630
You developed it?

456
00:27:00,870 --> 00:27:01,630
Do you like it?

457
00:27:01,630 --> 00:27:02,090
Yeah.

458
00:27:02,350 --> 00:27:03,240
It looks good.

459
00:27:03,430 --> 00:27:04,690
It's very meaningful.

460
00:27:06,080 --> 00:27:06,560
Yi Lan.

461
00:27:08,870 --> 00:27:10,330
I remember you once told me

462
00:27:11,150 --> 00:27:14,150
that photography is
how I communicate with the world.

463
00:27:17,590 --> 00:27:18,520
But actually...

464
00:27:19,590 --> 00:27:21,670
when I took photos before,

465
00:27:22,190 --> 00:27:23,320
I was always unhappy

466
00:27:23,390 --> 00:27:24,990
and full of negative energy.

467
00:27:25,910 --> 00:27:27,970
You were the one who stayed by my side,

468
00:27:29,390 --> 00:27:30,250
encouraged me,

469
00:27:31,430 --> 00:27:33,760
and brought so much positivity to my life.

470
00:27:33,800 --> 00:27:34,910
So I want to tell you

471
00:27:36,430 --> 00:27:37,240
that you are

472
00:27:37,240 --> 00:27:39,870
my other way of
communicating with this world.

473
00:27:41,630 --> 00:27:42,230
Thank you.

474
00:27:44,390 --> 00:27:45,070
Of course.

475
00:27:45,390 --> 00:27:46,670
We're best friends.

476
00:27:47,150 --> 00:27:47,670
Then...

477
00:27:47,950 --> 00:27:48,810
I'll get going.

478
00:27:48,910 --> 00:27:49,380
Yi Lan!

479
00:27:56,110 --> 00:27:57,510
Is there something else?

480
00:27:59,560 --> 00:28:00,430
What's wrong?

481
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:02,390
Just say it already.

482
00:28:06,350 --> 00:28:07,190
I like you.
